June 19/2003<br>
Editorial by: Scott Noseworthy (MFP)<br>
<br>
In today’s Pfosten Grossenberg, the main news service of the Republic of Slobovia, it was stated that “The economy [of Slobovia] was still born, the activity [of the nation has] dropped, and Slobovia has been experiencing negative-population growth.” It seems that Slobovia has gone down the road to inactivity again, much like the Kingdom of Ayllu and the Federated States. The latter two nations were the previous Troy Thompson projects before the latest incarnation of his pet project, Slobovia. <br>
<br>
The downward spiral of Slobovia (episode infinity) was not unexpected. In fact, most everyone in the micronational world expected it to fail. The reason is painfully simple – Troy Thompson is a terrible leader. Of course, to be fair, Thompson does show some initiative in trying to make a successful micronation for the first couple of weeks or so of the endeavour. Once the initial “excitement” of participating in a Troy project evaporates, the activity of the nation always comes crashing down. Instead of being a real leader and keeping the nation active on his own initiative, Thompson is always trying to get the rest of the population involved to save the nation. He fails to realize that if you want a nation to work, the leader must show a lot of interest and put a lot of work into the nation. That way, the nation can develop and look more attractive to interested parties, whereas a nation with an incompetent leader is doomed.<br>
<br>
Slobovia today is plagued with inactivity and as such, instead of trying to inspire the populace, Thompson is dissolving the Reichstag (the parliament), reducing cabinet, and for gawd only knows what reason, he’s focusing on establishing security agencies. What he needs to do as a leader in times of crisis is take hold of the situation by the horns and tackle the problems with some effort, instead of closing parliament or reducing cabinet and hoping that those moves alone solve the problem, which they will never do. <br>
<br>
The current laid back, “I’ll do this, and hopefully, through some Divine miracle, Slobovia will be saved” attitude shown by Thompson is the reason why all his micronations have been complete failures. It is the duty of the leader to step in when the population is not very active, and to take on the duty of running the country. Such is the case in Attera. Our population that wasn’t deployed to Iraq was having trouble staying active, so me, as the leader of Attera, had to take on all aspects of running the government and the nation for the most part. It’s an increase in workload, but at least the nation is still alive and important functions like domestic projects and foreign affairs are getting done. <br>
<br>
Just to prove my point, in the thread at the Slobovian ezboard in which inactivity was mentioned by Thompson earlier this month, he commented “Come on people...we don't exactly need to go inactive now!” This is exactly the behaviour I’m talking about – complaining about inactivity isn’t going to help your nation. <br>
<br>
A leader should not sit on his ass when the population is inactive and wait for them to become active again. A leader is always <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>leading </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->and the population will be active again when they please. In other words, the leader does not wait for the population to be active, he/she leads so that the efforts he/she makes in the nation will inspire the rest of the population to become active again.<br>
<br>
Thompson has a lot of good qualities which would be good for cabinet, and if he is truly dedicated to the success of Slobovia, he’ll use those qualities to improve it from the cabinet. Step down one level to cabinet Troy, and let someone with leadership skills take the step up. <br>
<br>
I would like to say that Thompson has two choices (get active or get out), however, history has proven that he possesses no leadership skills unfortunately – he’s simply a follower who always wants to be the leader, as Archetype said. Another person, Bobby (the Politikan) commented that “All [Slobovia] is, is a nation for the sole purpose for Troy to lead.” That person was very true, since Slobovia, like the rest of his nations, are simply there for Thompson to rule, and thus they fail.<br>
<br>
Put the nation before yourself for a change Thompson, or we’ll all just have to keep reading the same, mundane, highly predictable, history regarding your states (or to be more accurate, your failed states). <br>
<br>
Cheers<br>
